---
import Button from '../../Button.astro';
---

<section class="py-24 md:py-36 bg-warm-cream">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <p class="text-storehouse-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase">
          Who's behind Storehouse
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Divider -->
      <div class="my-10 flex justify-center reveal">
        <div class="w-16 h-px bg-text-faint/30"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bio prose -->
      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-text-body leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <p>
          I've spent 20+ years in real estate &mdash; as an agent, a sales
          manager, and a broker. I watched Bob's lesson play out hundreds of
          times. Families who left margin thrived. Families who maxed out
          every dollar struggled the moment anything shifted.
        </p>
        <p>
          That pattern stuck with me because I'm living it too. I'm a husband
          and a dad, and our family runs on the same hierarchy Storehouse is
          built around: give first, save second, spend what remains. It's not
          a formula I invented. It's what the Bible teaches about money, and
          it works.
        </p>
        <p>
          Storehouse is one expression of that conviction. I'm also building
          <span class="font-semibold text-text-deep">The Candid Agent</span>
          <span class="text-text-muted"> &mdash; honest real estate guidance</span> &mdash; and
          <span class="font-semibold text-text-deep">Good News Garden</span>
          <span class="text-text-muted"> &mdash; faith, family, and flourishing</span>.
          Different projects, same root: margin over maximum. Stewardship
          over consumption.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Sign off -->
      <div class="mt-12 reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <div class="w-12 h-px bg-text-faint/40"></div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-quote text-xl text-text-deep italic">
              Thanks for being here.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-lg text-text-muted">
              &mdash; JR
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTAs -->
      <div class="mt-16 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center reveal reveal-delay-3">
        <Button href="/waitlist" variant="primary" size="lg">
          Join the Waitlist
        </Button>
        <Button href="/philosophy" variant="secondary" size="lg">
          Read My Philosophy
        </Button>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>
